+{"type":"message","id":"76c7db22","parentId":"097055ec","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:07:45.322Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Plan overview:\n{\n  \"goal\": \"Build the Weekly Commit Module v1 — a production micro-frontend (TypeScript/React) with Java 21 modular-monolith backend replacing 15Five for weekly planning. Implements structured weekly commitments with RCDO strategy linkage, chess-layer prioritization, lock/reconcile lifecycle with immutable snapshots, explicit carry-forward with provenance, native tickets with status workflow, manager team dashboard with exception review, conservative explainable AI assistance, rules-based notifications, derived read models for reporting, and comprehensive audit logging. Delivered as a route-level Module Federation remote integrated into the PA host app. Note: The PRD recommends Java 21 (§22) and all checks are npm-based; the monorepo root package.json orchestrates both the TypeScript frontend (Vite/React) and Java backend (Gradle) via shell-out scripts. SQL migrations use Flyway against PostgreSQL.\",\n  \"totalSteps\": 20,\n  \"stepTitles\": [\n    \"1. Monorepo scaffolding and build infrastructure\",\n    \"2. Domain model types, enums, and database schema\",\n    \"3. RCDO hierarchy management API\",\n    \"4. Weekly plan creation and commit CRUD API\",\n    \"5. Lock lifecycle and baseline snapshot API\",\n    \"6. Post-lock scope change and reconciliation API\",\n    \"7. Carry-forward and ticket/work item API\",\n    \"8. Team weekly view, manager review, and permissions API\",\n    \"9. Frontend micro-frontend setup and routing\",\n    \"10. RCDO management UI\",\n    \"11. My Week page with commit list and capacity meter\",\n    \"12. Lock flow and reconcile view UI\",\n    \"13. Team Week dashboard UI\",\n    \"14. Tickets UI and search/filter/history views\",\n    \"15. Notifications backend and frontend panel\",\n    \"16. AI provider abstraction and commit assistance\",\n    \"17. AI risk detection and reconciliation assistance\",\n    \"18. Derived read models and operational reporting\",\n    \"19. Configuration management and admin settings\",\n    \"20. Audit logging, accessibility, and integration polish\"\n  ]\n}\n\nPrevious step 3 (RCDO hierarchy management API) has been completed and approved.\nFiles changed in the previous step:\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/cost.json\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/observations.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/sessions/continuous/relay-a/2026-03-24T04-23-35-130Z_4c4202d2-9023-459a-b908-dfaede19919d.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/sessions/continuous/relay-b/2026-03-24T04-35-30-972Z_471484d6-96e0-4a6b-86fc-b9b081fa294f.jsonl\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/state.json\nbackend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/domain/repository/RcdoChangeLogRepository.java\nbackend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/domain/repository/RcdoNodeRepository.java\n.pi/duet/runs/2026-03-24T03-49-04-151Z-dd75a832/steps/3\nbackend/src/main/java/com/weeklycommit/rcdo\nbackend/src/test/java/com/weeklycommit/rcdo\nbackend/src/test/resources/mockito-extensions\n\nYour session has context from prior steps. The repository may have changed since your last turn.\nBefore making assumptions about file contents, verify the current state of any files you need to modify.\nDo NOT re-read files that are unrelated to the current step.\n\nStep 4: Weekly plan creation and commit CRUD API\n{\n  \"id\": \"step-4\",\n  \"title\": \"Weekly plan creation and commit CRUD API\",\n  \"description\": \"Implement weekly plan and commit CRUD per PRD §13 FR-1, FR-2.\\n\\n**WeeklyPlanService:**\\n- `getOrCreatePlan(userId, weekStartDate)`: returns existing plan or lazily creates a DRAFT plan. Enforces exactly one plan per user per week (unique constraint). Snapshots home team and configured capacity budget onto the plan.\\n- `getPlan(planId)`: returns plan with commits ordered by priority.\\n- `getMyCurrentWeekPlan(userId)`: resolves current week and delegates to getOrCreate.\\n- Week-start date calculation using configurable cadence (default: Monday).\\n\\n**CommitService:**\\n- `createCommit(planId, commitData)`: validates plan is DRAFT, assigns next priority order. Validates chess piece limits across the plan (max 1 King, max 2 Queen). Validates estimate points ∈ {1,2,3,5,8}.\\n- `updateCommit(commitId, commitData)`: validates plan is DRAFT. Re-validates chess piece limits if piece changed.\\n- `deleteCommit(commitId)`: validates plan is DRAFT. Reorders remaining commits.\\n- `reorderCommits(planId, orderedCommitIds)`: validates plan is DRAFT. Sets new priority order.\\n- RCDO linkage validation: delegates to RcdoService helper (Outcome-first, DO fallback, no Rally Cry). If commit has a linked ticket with RCDO and commit RCDO is blank, default from ticket.\\n- Success criteria required for King and Queen chess pieces.\\n\\n**REST controllers:**\\n- `GET/POST /api/plans` — list user plans, create/get-or-create plan\\n- `GET /api/plans/{id}` — plan detail with commits\\n- `POST /api/plans/{id}/commits` — create commit\\n- `PUT /api/plans/{id}/commits/{commitId}` — update commit\\n- `DELETE /api/plans/{id}/commits/{commitId}` — delete commit\\n- `PUT /api/plans/{id}/commits/reorder` — reorder commits\\n\\n**Unit tests:** one-plan-per-user-per-week, chess piece limits, estimate validation, RCDO linkage rules, priority reorder, success criteria requirement for King/Queen.\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"lint\",\n    \"typecheck\",\n    \"unit\",\n    \"build\"\n  ]\n}\n\nYou are the first agent to work on this step.\nImplement the changes described above, run checks to verify, and fix any issues before handing off.\nBe thorough — the next agent will review your work and should find it correct.\n\nPrior observations from earlier steps (address if they fall within this step's scope):\n- [MEDIUM] step 1 backend/build.gradle.kts: U